<!-- 
    ADOPTION CARD CODE
    BY PANDAPPUCCINO
    
    == WHAT IS THIS? ==
    A simple adoption code that I threw together for funsies, since I plan to sell adoptables soon! The code is a "card" so you can place multiples into the same page, like a one-stop shop. Mobile-friendly, too!
    
    The code includes samples for editing a card to show that an adoptable has already been sold or is on hold.
    
    == HOW DO I USE IT? ==
    Just edit each section as needed!.
    
    == WHAT'S THE CATCH? ==
    Just keep my credit intact; that's all I ask..
    
    == COMMON EDITING TIPS ==
    1) You can change the particular Bootstrap colors by replacing the color classes (such as bg-dark).  If you would prefer to remove the Bootstrap colors and use your own colors, just remove the entire color class and, in the given "style" section, add "background:" followed by a color, either a hex color or rgb/rgba value.
    2) You can remove the capitalization of the titles by removing the "text-uppercase" class from a given section.
    3) You can use inline color styling by using <span></span> tags in tandem with either Bootstrap color classes or custom color styling.
    4) You can adjust the width of any element with Bootstrap classes by replacing the "w-75" class with another number.  For more precise styling, you can remove the class and style the widths directly; however, they may not look as good on mobile screens!
	
-->

